<I>Bristlebane</I><BR>
<I>Grand Master Tailor, Brewer, and Jeweler</I><BR>
<I>Kung Fu Druid  :)</I></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphreaky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phreaky</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0> at: 6/12/01 9:04:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udreth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreth1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 1:43:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2480.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to get rare spells</span><hr size=1> While I bow to your masterfulness, I DID get raiding groups to Guardian Wurms in Skyfire on many different occasions, with no luck. Many other classes got level 59-60 spells, but as far as the druids along for the trip...we did not. Er, maybe one spirit of oak. However, after a few trips people ge their spells and the tanks want to go where tank loot is. As I, and some others, do not play 8 hours a day, it can prove difficult to get a couple groups to actually go to skyfire. My $$$ solution was simply an observation that money is the vaseline of social intercourse, Phreaky.<br>
<br>
Ergo- I am fully aware of skyfire spell drops thank you. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udreth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreth1</A> at: 6/12/01 10:51:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umeg26.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meg26</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 3:53:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2480.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to get rare spells</span><hr size=1> Talendor has dropped all of my lvl 60 spells from Kunark.  so if you're looking for those, that's a good place.  other places for 54-60 spells are juggs/reets in OS and the emporer in OS occasionally drops them, seen spirit of oak and mask of the hunter from him.  chardok royal guards sometimes drop spells, seen stuff like succor down there, but that's more common.  Dragons are your best source for 60 spells though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showPrevMessage?topicID=2480.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showNextMessage?topicID=2480.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2480.topic&index=6><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.emailToFriend?topicID=2480.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><b